name: Snivy
flavorText: It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Maractus
flavorText: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokemon that prey on its flower seeds.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Tepig
flavorText: It blows fire through its nose. When it catches a cold, the fire becomes pitch-black smoke instead.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Oshawott
flavorText: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Alomomola
flavorText: Floating in the open sea is how they live. When they find a wounded Pokemon, they embrace it and bring it to shore.

name: Blitzle
flavorText: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use their flashing manes to communicate with one another.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Munna
flavorText: It eats the dreams of people and Pokemon. When it eats a pleasant dream, it expels pink-colored mist.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Sandile
flavorText: It moves along below the sand's surface, except for its nose and eyes. A dark membrane shields its eyes from the sun.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Zorua
flavorText: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Klink
flavorText: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, attach an Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.

name: Pidove
flavorText: These Pokemon live in cities. They are accustomed to people. Flocks often gather in parks and plazas.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokemon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Audino
flavorText: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads.
